column1: Completions by Award Type and Level
The completions reporting year is between July 1 and June 30.
column13:
This table tracks degree and certificate completions by award type and level from 1988–89 through 2024–25. It separates completions into Bachelor’s, Master’s, Doctoral, and various certificate categories (postsecondary below the baccalaureate, post-baccalaureate, and post-master’s). The data show steady growth over time, with Bachelor’s completions rising from about 1,460 in 1988–89 to peaks above 1,900 in the mid-2010s, while Master’s completions have generally stayed between 400–600 annually.

Abbreviations/Notes:

Postsecondary (below the baccalaureate) = certificates requiring less than a 4-year degree.

Post-baccalaureate = advanced undergraduate-level certificate earned after a bachelor’s.

Post-master’s = certificate earned after a master’s degree.

column1: *In 2011-12 and 2012-13, some certificates did not qualify for IPEDS reporting because the number of required credits was below the mininum for a post-baccaulaureate or post-master's certificate.  CCSU's figures does include those certificates not reported to IPEDS therefore figures will not match IPEDS reporting for those years.
Data Source: IPEDS Data Center and Fact Book Completions Query
